        "children": [
          {
            "id": "cat_architecture",
            "label": "Architecture",
            "type": "label",
            "count": 10,
            "children": [
              {
                "id": "rule_11",
                "type": "rule",
                "content": {
                  "text": "1. **Kubernetes Controller** (`internal/kubernetes/agent/`)\n   - Watches K8s resources using controller-runtime\n   - Implements event-driven reconciliation\n   - Handles resource indexing and storage\n   - Supports leader election for HA",
                  "originalHeader": "Core Components"
                },
                "metadata": {
                  "strength": "SHOULD",
                  "format": "ListItem",
                  "line_start": 24,
                  "line_end": 28
                }
              },
              {
                "id": "rule_12",
                "type": "rule",
                "content": {
                  "text": "2. **Intake Worker** (`internal/intake/`)\n   - gRPC streaming client for data upload\n   - Batches deltas for efficient transmission\n   - Handles retry logic and stream recovery\n   - Implements heartbeat mechanism",
                  "originalHeader": "Core Components"
                },
                "metadata": {
                  "strength": "SHOULD",
                  "format": "ListItem",
                  "line_start": 30,
                  "line_end": 34
                }
              },
              {
                "id": "rule_13",
                "type": "rule",
                "content": {
                  "text": "3. **Performance Monitoring** (`pkg/performance/`)\n   - Collector architecture for system metrics\n   - Supports both one-shot and continuous collection\n   - Reads from /proc and /sys filesystems\n   - Provides LoadStats, MemoryStats, CPUStats, etc.",
                  "originalHeader": "Core Components"
                },
                "metadata": {
                  "strength": "SHOULD",
                  "format": "ListItem",
                  "line_start": 36,
                  "line_end": 40
                }
              },
              {
                "id": "rule_14",
                "type": "rule",
                "content": {
                  "text": "4. **Resource Store** (`pkg/resource/store/`)\n   - BadgerDB-backed storage for resource state\n   - Supports resources and relationships (RDF triplets)\n   - Event-driven subscription model\n   - Efficient indexing and querying",
                  "originalHeader": "Core Components"
                },
                "metadata": {
                  "strength": "SHOULD",
                  "format": "ListItem",
                  "line_start": 42,
                  "line_end": 46
                }
              },
              {
                "id": "rule_15",
                "type": "rule",
                "content": {
                  "text": "5. **Cloud Provider Abstractions** (`internal/kubernetes/cluster/`)\n   - Interface for different cloud providers\n   - EKS implementation with auto-discovery\n   - KIND support for local development\n   - Extensible for GKE, AKS future support",
                  "originalHeader": "Core Components"
                },
                "metadata": {
                  "strength": "SHOULD",
                  "format": "ListItem",
                  "line_start": 48,
                  "line_end": 52
                }
              },
              {
                "id": "rule_16",
                "type": "rule",
                "content": {
                  "text": "The performance monitoring system follows a dual-interface pattern:",
                  "originalHeader": "Collector Interface Design"
                },
                "metadata": {
                  "strength": "SHOULD",
                  "format": "Paragraph",
                  "line_start": 107,
                  "line_end": 107
                }
              },
              {
                "id": "rule_17",
                "type": "rule",
                "content": {
                  "text": "- **In-memory storage** for development/testing\n- **Event-driven subscriptions** for real-time updates\n- **RDF triplet relationships** (subject, predicate, object)\n- **Efficient indexing** for complex queries",
                  "originalHeader": "BadgerDB Integration"
                },
                "metadata": {
                  "strength": "SHOULD",
                  "format": "ListItem",
                  "line_start": 163,
                  "line_end": 166
                }
              },
              {
                "id": "rule_18",
                "type": "rule",
                "content": {
                  "text": "- **Streaming gRPC** for efficient data upload\n- **Batched deltas** with configurable batch sizes\n- **Exponential backoff** for connection failures\n- **Stream recovery** with automatic reconnection\n- **Heartbeat mechanism** for connection health",
                  "originalHeader": "Intake Service Communication"
                },
                "metadata": {
                  "strength": "SHOULD",
                  "format": "ListItem",
                  "line_start": 185,
                  "line_end": 189
                }
              },
              {
                "id": "rule_19",
                "type": "rule",
                "content": {
                  "text": "1. K8s events → Controller → Resource Store\n2. Resource Store → Event Router → Intake Worker\n3. Intake Worker → Batching → gRPC Stream → Antimetal",
                  "originalHeader": "Data Flow"
                },
                "metadata": {
                  "strength": "SHOULD",
                  "format": "ListItem",
                  "line_start": 192,
                  "line_end": 194
                }
              },
              {
                "id": "rule_20",
                "type": "rule",
                "content": {
                  "text": "Place `//go:generate` directives in the userspace packages that will use the eBPF programs, rather than in a centralized location. This keeps the generation logic co-located with the code that uses it.",
                  "originalHeader": "Generation Pattern"
                },
                "metadata": {
                  "strength": "MUST",
                  "format": "Paragraph",
                  "line_start": 280,
                  "line_end": 280
                }
              }
